    "body": "The order here is basically just the order of actual processing, because head update happens while we're processing the block, and we notify of a block once we've completely imported and updated fork choice...\n\nI could potentially delay notification that head has updated, but it'd be specifically for this event stream, most of the rest of the system really does want head changes asap, so it'd be a synthetic delay in notifying external parties of head being updated...\n\nOther than that i'd have to assume a block is going to completely import correctly and notify that earlier, but that could also be inaccurate if incorporating the block fails...\nI'm not really sold on either answer, so I figured I'd update the ticket and see how strongly you feel about this being an odd order...",
